https://leetcode.com/problems/group-anagrams/description/

QUESTION:
Input: strs = ["eat","tea","tan","ate","nat","bat"]

Output: [["bat"],["nat","tan"],["ate","eat","tea"]]
SOLUTION:
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n* klogk)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n*k)
1)create a hasmap that can store values
2)loopp through the string
3)sort each string and check if it is in the map.
4)if yes then just add the value or create a new arraylist.

Things to remember are the string compare,valueof.

CODE:
class Solution {
    public List<List<String>> groupAnagrams(String[] strs) {
        HashMap<String,List<String>>map=new HashMap<>();
        for(int i=0;i<strs.length;i++){
            char ch[]=strs[i].toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(ch);
            String val=String.valueOf(ch);
            if(!map.containsKey(val)){
                map.put(val,new ArrayList<>());
            }
            map.get(val).add(strs[i]);
        }
        return new ArrayList<>(map.values());

    }
}
